The $\beta$-asymmetry parameter $A_\mathit{Wu}=1/3$ for a $2^+ \rightarrow 2^+$ Gamow-Teller transition.
Therefore,  to good approximation, the count rate in the $\beta$-particle detectors is 
$R_{L(R)}^\pm \propto 1\mp(\pm) A_\mathit{Wu} P $, 
where the signs depend on the direction of the polarization ($\pm$) and the place (\textit{L/R}) of the detector.
